(102, 1, 'Sundar Kaand', '&lt;h3&gt;&lt;marquee behavior=&quot;scroll&quot; direction=&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(255, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;This is to inform to all our valuable customers that Booking for Flowers, Puja Kits, Prasad Kit, Monthly Puja Kit will start from 27th June 2016&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/marquee&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;There are many gods we worship for their divinity and powers in \r\nHinduism. But there is only one god - Lord Hanuman, who is known for his\r\n unwavered faith and selfless devotion to Lord Rama. &lt;strong&gt;Sundarkand Paath&lt;/strong&gt;\r\n is a recitation of one of the seven sections of Ramayana that depict \r\nand describe Lord Hanuman’s devotion along with stories of valour, \r\nwisdom, faith and strength. The literal translation of Sundarkand is a \r\n‘Beautiful Story’. Penned by Saint Tulsidas Goswami in a collection of \r\nChopais – religious poetry, it narrates all of Lord Hanuman’s endeavours\r\n including the epic journey across the ocean to Lanka to convey Lord \r\nRama’s message to Devi Sita.&lt;/p&gt;', 'Sundar Kaand', '', '', '', ''),
